    <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="classMR_1_1Laplacian" kindref="compound">Laplacian</ref> to smoothly deform a region preserving mesh fine details. How to use: </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Initialize <ref refid="classMR_1_1Laplacian" kindref="compound">Laplacian</ref> for the region being deformed, here region properties are remembered.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Change positions of some vertices within the region and call fixVertex for them.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Optionally call <ref refid="classMR_1_1Laplacian_1a6ab6466ee01c85f49d6bfd5955ba7de0" kindref="member">updateSolver()</ref></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Call <ref refid="classMR_1_1Laplacian_1adec94b8812ff2f12bbe9e564894393f4" kindref="member">apply()</ref> to change the remaining vertices within the region Then steps 1-4 or 2-4 can be repeated. <programlisting filename="cpp-samples/LaplacianDeformation.cpp"></programlisting> Generated from class <computeroutput><ref refid="classMR_1_1Laplacian" kindref="compound">MR.Laplacian</ref></computeroutput>. This is the non-const half of the class. </para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
